{"name": "pytest-servers", "metadata": {"name": "pytest-servers", "version": "0.5.9", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 3 - Alpha", "Framework :: Pytest", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9"], "home_page": null, "license": "Apache-2.0", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["pytest", "requests", "fsspec", "universal-pathlib", "filelock"], "summary": "pytest servers", "upload_time": 1735437865}, "documentation": ["---\nsubstitutions:\n  Black: |-\n    ```{image} https://img.shields.io/badge/code%20style-black-000000.svg\n    :alt: Black\n    :target: https://github.com/psf/black\n    ```\n  Codecov: |-\n    ```{image} https://codecov.io/gh/iterative/pytest-servers/branch/main/graph/badge.svg\n    :alt: Codecov\n    :target: https://app.codecov.io/gh/iterative/pytest-servers\n    ```\n  License: |-\n    ```{image} https://img.shields.io/pypi/l/pytest-servers\n    :alt: License\n    :target: https://opensource.org/licenses/Apache-2.0\n    ```\n  PyPI: |-\n    ```{image} https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/pytest-servers.svg\n    :alt: PyPI\n    :target: https://pypi.org/project/pytest-servers/\n    ```\n  Python Version: |-\n    ```{image} https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/pytest-servers\n    :alt: Python Version\n    :target: https://pypi.org/project/pytest-servers\n    ```\n  Status: |-\n    ```{image} https://img.shields.io/pypi/status/pytest-servers.svg\n    :alt: Status\n    :target: https://pypi.org/project/pytest-servers/\n    ```\n  Tests: |-\n    ```{image} https://github.com/iterative/pytest-servers/workflows/Tests/badge.svg\n    :alt: Tests\n    :target: https://github.com/iterative/pytest-servers/actions?workflow=Tests\n    ```\n  pre-commit: |-\n    ```{image} https://img.shields.io/badge/pre--commit-enabled-brightgreen?logo=pre-commit&logoColor=white\n    :alt: pre-commit\n    :target: https://github.com/pre-commit/pre-commit\n    ```\n---\n\n# pytest servers\n\n{{ PyPI }} {{ Status }} {{ Python Version }} {{ License }}\n\n{{ Tests }} {{ Codecov }} {{ pre-commit }} {{ Black }}\n\n# Features\n\nCreate temporary directories on the following filesystems:\n\n- Local fs\n- In-memory fs\n- S3, both using mock S3 remotes (<https://github.com/spulec/moto>) and real S3 remotes\n- Azure, both using mock Azure remotes (<https://github.com/Azure/Azurite>) via docker and using real Azure Storage remotes\n- Google Cloud Storage, both using mock GCS remote (<https://github.com/fsouza/fake-gcs-server>) via docker and using real Google Storage Remotes\n\n# Installation\n\nYou can install *pytest servers* via [pip] from [PyPI]:\n\n```console\n$ pip install pytest-servers\n```\n\nTo use temporary S3 paths:\n\n```console\n$ pip install pytest-servers[s3]\n```\n\nTo use temporary Azure paths\n\n```console\n$ pip install pytest-servers[azure]\n```\n\nTo use temporary Google Cloud Storage paths\n\n```console\n$ pip install pytest-servers[gcs]\n```\n\nTo install all extras:\n\n```console\n$ pip install pytest-servers[all]\n```\n\n# Usage\n\nThe main fixture provided by `pytest-servers` provides is `tmp_upath_factory`, which can be used\nto generate temporary paths on different (mocked) filesystems:\n\n```python\ndef test_something_on_s3(tmp_upath_factory):\n    path = tmp_upath_factory.mktemp(\"s3\")\n    foo = path / \"foo\"\n    foo.write_text(\"foo\")\n    ...\n```\n\n`mktemp` supports the following filesystem types:\n\n- `local` (local filesystem)\n- `memory` (in-memory filesystem)\n- `s3` (Amazon S3)\n- `gcs` (Google Cloud Storage)\n- `azure` (Azure Storage)\n\nSome convenience fixtures that wrap `tmp_upath_factory.mktemp` and return a paths on these filesystems are also available:\n\n- `tmp_local_path`\n- `tmp_memory_path`\n- `tmp_s3_path`\n- `tmp_gcs_path`\n- `tmp_azure_path`\n\nThe `tmp_upath` fixture can be used for parametrizing paths with pytest's indirect parametrization:\n\n```python\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"tmp_upath\", [\"local\", \"s3\", \"gcs\", \"gs\"], indirect=True)\ndef test_something(tmp_upath):\n    pass\n```\n\nIn order to use real remotes instead of mocked ones, use `tmp_upath_factory` with the following methods\n\n- `tmp_upath_factory.s3(region_name, client_kwargs)` where client_kwargs are passed to the underlying S3FileSystem/boto client\n- `tmp_upath_factory.gcs(endpoint_url)`\n- `tmp_upath_factory.azure(connection_string)`\n\nVersioning support can be used by using the `versioning` fixture. This is currently supported for s3 and gcs remotes\n\n```python\n# using mktemp\ndef test_something_on_s3_versioned(tmp_upath_factory):\n    path = tmp_upath_factory.mktemp(\"s3\", version_aware=True)\n    assert path.fs.version_aware # bucket has versioning enabled\n\n# or, using remote-specific fixtures\ndef test_something_on_s3_versioned(tmp_s3_path, versioning):\n    assert tmp_s3_path.fs.version_aware # bucket has versioning enabled\n```\n\n# Contributing\n\nContributions are very welcome.\nTo learn more, see the [Contributor Guide].\n\n# License\n\nDistributed under the terms of the [Apache 2.0 license],\n*pytest servers* is free and open source software.\n\n# Issues\n\nIf you encounter any problems,\nplease [file an issue] along with a detailed description.\n\n% github-only\n\n[apache 2.0 license]: https://opensource.org/licenses/Apache-2.0\n[contributor guide]: CONTRIBUTING.rst\n[file an issue]: https://github.com/iterative/pytest-servers/issues\n[pip]: https://pip.pypa.io/\n[pypi]: https://pypi.org/\n"], "modules": [{"name": "pytest_servers.gcs", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "pytest_servers.gcs.fake_gcs_server", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "docker_client", "type": {"name": "DockerClient", "xref": {"fqname": "docker.DockerClient", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "tmp_path_factory", "type": {"name": "pytest.TempPathFactory", "xref": {"fqname": "pytest.TempPathFactory", "project": "pytest"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Spins up a fake-gcs-server container. Returns the endpoint URL."]}], "variables": [{"name": "pytest_servers.gcs.logger", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pytest_servers.gcs.GCS_DEFAULT_PORT", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "pytest_servers.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "pytest_servers.utils.wait_until", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "pred", "type": {"name": "Callable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Callable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "...", "xref": null, "params": null}, {"name": "_T", "xref": {"fqname": "_T", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "timeout", "type": {"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "pause", "type": {"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "_T", "xref": {"fqname": "_T", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pytest_servers.utils.random_string", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "n", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pytest_servers.utils.monkeypatch_session", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "pytest.MonkeyPatch", "xref": {"fqname": "pytest.MonkeyPatch", "project": "pytest"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Session-scoped monkeypatch."]},